description:
This work reimagines Judith Beheading Holofernes through a playful and contemporary lens. Drawing from the dramatic intensity and chiaroscuro of Caravaggio, the piece transforms the original narrative into a whimsical yet layered allegory of revelation and disguise. 
    },
    {
    In this reinterpretation, Judith's decisive act is prompted not by political or heroic necessity, but by an unexpected and almost absurd chain of discovery: a domestic moment in which her cat captures a mouse, the mouse uncovers sunflower seeds, and the seeds ultimately expose her lover as a Minotaur in disguise. The intrusion of the uncanny into the intimate space reframes the scene, merging humor with tension. 
    },
    {
      By juxtaposing Baroque drama with surreal storytelling, the work explores themes of perception, hidden identity, and the fragile boundary between the ordinary and the fantastical.
